1
00:00:02,046 --> 00:00:06,083
You lose,
we don't merge.

2
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:08,135
You win,
you get what you want.

3
00:00:08,202 --> 00:00:10,087
You lose,
you stay.

4
00:00:10,171 --> 00:00:12,305
You extend
your noncompete,

5
00:00:12,373 --> 00:00:16,009
and you get a chance to earn
your name on the door,

6
00:00:16,060 --> 00:00:18,044
because it's not
going up there now.

7
00:00:18,096 --> 00:00:19,379
There's no room
for both of us.

8
00:00:19,430 --> 00:00:22,716
Unless we made room
for each other.

9
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:24,434
I put him on the list,
and I handed it in.

10
00:00:24,519 --> 00:00:27,437
He didn't put you
on his list.

11
00:00:27,522 --> 00:00:28,905
- I won't.
- You will.

12
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:30,190
Harvey will never
forgive me.

13
00:00:30,241 --> 00:00:31,881
This is a letter
to the district attorney,

14
00:00:31,909 --> 00:00:35,362
saying that you
are breaking the law.

15
00:00:35,413 --> 00:00:38,915
You file your motion,

16
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,367
I'll file mine.

17
00:00:40,418 --> 00:00:41,501
You weren't there.

18
00:00:41,569 --> 00:00:42,890
- I didn't have to be.
- Jessica--

19
00:00:42,903 --> 00:00:44,454
You don't work for Jessica.
You work for me.

20
00:00:44,539 --> 00:00:47,240
You're fired.
No, he's not.

21
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:48,925
You could've just told me
that you didn't love me

22
00:00:49,010 --> 00:00:50,577
instead of selling me out.

23
00:00:50,628 --> 00:00:52,512
I didn't sell you out,
Scottie.

24
00:00:52,580 --> 00:00:54,297
I just got fired.

25
00:00:54,382 --> 00:00:55,799
Whatever she did,

26
00:00:55,883 --> 00:00:57,523
you wouldn't have this merger
without her.

27
00:00:57,585 --> 00:01:00,520
Would you have her work here
or in London?

28
00:01:00,588 --> 00:01:02,589
You're going
to stay here,

29
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,775
be humble,

30
00:01:04,859 --> 00:01:06,693
and learn
your goddamn place.

31
00:01:06,761 --> 00:01:09,229
I never went
to Harvard.

32
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:10,230
What?

33
00:01:10,281 --> 00:01:13,066
I'm a fraud.

34
00:01:50,104 --> 00:01:51,137
Hey.

35
00:01:51,189 --> 00:01:52,589
I got your message.
What's going on?

36
00:01:52,607 --> 00:01:55,776
Partners meeting.
Essential personnel only.

37
00:01:55,827 --> 00:01:56,867
In the middle
of the night?

38
00:01:56,911 --> 00:01:58,445
You afraid
of the dark?

39
00:01:58,496 --> 00:01:59,830
I wouldn't be if I had
my Cookie Monster with me.

40
00:01:59,914 --> 00:02:01,081
Well, then go get him,

41
00:02:01,148 --> 00:02:03,917
because we're finalizing
the terms of the merger.

42
00:02:03,984 --> 00:02:04,918
We?

43
00:02:04,985 --> 00:02:06,369
We.

44
00:02:06,454 --> 00:02:08,288
So I'm a partner now?

45
00:02:08,339 --> 00:02:09,706
Easy, Marcia Clark.

46
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:11,875
Jessica and I
discussed it.

47
00:02:11,959 --> 00:02:14,094
You're responsible
for making this merger happen.

48
00:02:14,161 --> 00:02:15,595
You deserve
to be here.

49
00:02:15,663 --> 00:02:17,764
So Jessica and you
talked?

50
00:02:17,832 --> 00:02:18,765
You forgave her?

51
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:20,834
She won.
I lost.

52
00:02:20,885 --> 00:02:21,852
Nothing to forgive.

53
00:02:21,936 --> 00:02:24,020
And me?

54
00:02:24,105 --> 00:02:27,224
You did
what you had to do.

55
00:02:29,176 --> 00:02:33,196
You have no idea
how much I needed to hear that.

56
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:37,067
The merger is complete.

57
00:02:37,151 --> 00:02:38,351
And we would like
to show everyone

58
00:02:38,402 --> 00:02:40,954
that the new Darby Pearson
will be stronger,

59
00:02:41,021 --> 00:02:42,355
better connected--

60
00:02:42,406 --> 00:02:44,791
And most importantly,
based on a foundation that is--

61
00:02:44,859 --> 00:02:45,909
Full of shit.

62
00:02:45,993 --> 00:02:46,993
What the hell's
going on?

63
00:02:47,044 --> 00:02:49,412
- I told her.
- Told her what?

64
00:02:49,497 --> 00:02:51,131
That Mike Ross
is a fraud,

65
00:02:51,198 --> 00:02:52,966
and I am not going
to let him get away with it.

66
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,084
How could you do this?

67
00:02:54,168 --> 00:02:56,536
You did this
to yourself.

68
00:03:05,179 --> 00:03:07,898
How long are you going
to keep staring at that offer?

69
00:03:07,982 --> 00:03:09,432
Until one of us blinks.

70
00:03:09,517 --> 00:03:11,184
Deron signed it.
You said it was great.

71
00:03:11,235 --> 00:03:12,519
I'm not interested
in great.

72
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:15,889
I want it to know
who its daddy is.

73
00:03:19,443 --> 00:03:20,660
What is it, Donna?

74
00:03:20,728 --> 00:03:24,497
It's Sunday night.
Darby needs an answer.

75
00:03:24,565 --> 00:03:27,000
London.
Send her to London.

76
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,909
Do you want
to talk about it?

77
00:03:38,296 --> 00:03:40,013
Have Ray
meet me downstairs.

78
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,015
And where should I say
you're going?

79
00:03:42,082 --> 00:03:44,100
Brooklyn.

80
00:04:04,372 --> 00:04:06,706
I did not expect
the great Harvey Specter

81
00:04:06,774 --> 00:04:07,707
to come all the way
to Brooklyn

82
00:04:07,775 --> 00:04:09,242
just to deliver
a contract.

83
00:04:09,293 --> 00:04:11,328
That's good,
'cause I came for the hot dogs.

84
00:04:11,412 --> 00:04:13,463
I told you,
that was our final offer.

85
00:04:13,547 --> 00:04:15,081
You did,
but the third quarter's

86
00:04:15,132 --> 00:04:16,750
about to end,
and if you want Deron Williams

87
00:04:16,801 --> 00:04:19,619
playing for you
in the fourth,

88
00:04:19,670 --> 00:04:22,222
this is his number.

89
00:04:23,841 --> 00:04:25,058
Even if you had
another offer,

90
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,459
which you don't,

91
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:29,145
he can't leave
in the middle of a game.

92
00:04:29,230 --> 00:04:30,730
I was talking
about the fourth quarter

93
00:04:30,798 --> 00:04:32,015
of game seven,

94
00:04:32,099 --> 00:04:33,900
when you're looking
to lock up a championship,

95
00:04:33,901 --> 00:04:36,903
because the question isn't
"do you want Deron or not?"

96
00:04:36,971 --> 00:04:39,639
It's "do you want
a ring or not?"

97
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:41,074
You got nothing.

98
00:04:41,141 --> 00:04:43,276
And I told you,
that's my final offer.

99
00:04:43,327 --> 00:04:44,277
Then I guess I'll just have
to go bring Deron

100
00:04:44,328 --> 00:04:45,445
his new Mavs jersey then.

101
00:04:45,496 --> 00:04:47,364
There's no way
Mark Cuban pays that much.

102
00:04:47,448 --> 00:04:48,648
Why don't you call him
and ask?

103
00:04:48,699 --> 00:04:51,284
Oh, wait, you can't,
because he hates you.

104
00:04:51,335 --> 00:04:52,285
Bullshit.

105
00:04:52,336 --> 00:04:53,370
We may not
be blood brothers,

106
00:04:53,454 --> 00:04:54,371
but he doesn't
hate me.

107
00:04:54,455 --> 00:04:55,872
Oh, he does now.

108
00:04:55,957 --> 00:05:00,260
Evidently, he found out
about that thing from last May.

109
00:05:00,327 --> 00:05:01,344
How do you know that?

110
00:05:01,429 --> 00:05:03,830
Because I was there
when I told him.

111
00:05:03,881 --> 00:05:05,598
You have
until 10:00 a.m.

112
00:05:05,666 --> 00:05:07,017
Then I'm calling Dallas.

113
00:05:07,101 --> 00:05:09,335
And Mark may not
take your call,

114
00:05:09,387 --> 00:05:13,356
but he'll sure as hell
take mine.

115
00:05:13,441 --> 00:05:14,607
How do I know
you're not going to turn around

116
00:05:14,675 --> 00:05:15,725
and get him
to pay more?

117
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:16,943
You don't.

118
00:05:17,011 --> 00:05:18,445
But if you don't
match this,

119
00:05:18,512 --> 00:05:20,897
you'll never find out.

120
00:05:35,029 --> 00:05:36,296
Jessica.

121
00:05:36,363 --> 00:05:37,330
Harvey.

122
00:05:37,381 --> 00:05:39,332
I don't recall
giving you my key.

123
00:05:39,383 --> 00:05:41,418
I don't recall authorizing you
to negotiate

124
00:05:41,502 --> 00:05:42,869
behind Deron Williams' back.

125
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,220
His back
is just fine.

126
00:05:44,305 --> 00:05:46,172
I'm standing
right behind it.

127
00:05:46,223 --> 00:05:49,709
Then why is the contract
he signed in my hand?

128
00:05:51,762 --> 00:05:52,979
How much
did you ask for?

129
00:05:53,047 --> 00:05:55,181
Triple.

130
00:05:55,232 --> 00:05:56,733
You out of your mind?

131
00:05:56,817 --> 00:05:57,767
We have leverage.

132
00:05:57,852 --> 00:06:00,353
And what is that?

133
00:06:00,404 --> 00:06:02,522
- It's complicated.
- Simplify it for me.

134
00:06:02,573 --> 00:06:04,724
- I bluffed him.
- That's not leverage.

135
00:06:04,775 --> 00:06:05,825
It is
if he believes it.

136
00:06:05,893 --> 00:06:07,444
And if it fails,
he fires us

137
00:06:07,528 --> 00:06:09,162
and takes ten other players
with him.

138
00:06:09,229 --> 00:06:10,830
Then it better not fail.

139
00:06:10,898 --> 00:06:13,616
You asked the man
for triple.

140
00:06:13,701 --> 00:06:15,581
If I had what I said I had,
that's what I'd get.

141
00:06:15,619 --> 00:06:18,204
I don't ask for triple,
he knows I'm bluffing.

142
00:06:18,255 --> 00:06:19,789
Then don't bluff
in the first place.

143
00:06:19,874 --> 00:06:22,675
I'm afraid
that's what I do.

144
00:06:22,743 --> 00:06:23,877
You know
what I think?

145
00:06:23,928 --> 00:06:25,178
I think you want it
to fail.

146
00:06:25,245 --> 00:06:26,596
I think
you're stuck

147
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,680
with a merger
you don't want

148
00:06:27,748 --> 00:06:29,682
and a noncompete
you can't stand,

149
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,384
and you're trying
to get me to fire you.

150
00:06:31,435 --> 00:06:33,269
I could bust
that noncompete wide open.

151
00:06:33,354 --> 00:06:34,637
But you gave me
your word.

152
00:06:34,722 --> 00:06:36,940
Which is
why I'm staying.

153
00:06:37,024 --> 00:06:39,442
Jessica, I've always
operated this way.

154
00:06:39,527 --> 00:06:42,195
It's what you hired me for,
it's what you pay me for,

155
00:06:42,262 --> 00:06:44,364
and it used to be
what you valued me for.

156
00:06:44,431 --> 00:06:45,565
I'm not going
to fire you.

157
00:06:45,616 --> 00:06:47,984
Neither is Deron Williams.

158
00:06:48,069 --> 00:06:49,452
Nets just caved.

159
00:06:49,537 --> 00:06:52,655
So unless you're looking
to cook me breakfast tomorrow,

160
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:54,207
I'd say we're done.

161
00:07:04,668 --> 00:07:06,469
I told you
I needed time.

162
00:07:06,554 --> 00:07:07,754
I know,
but it's been two days,

163
00:07:07,788 --> 00:07:08,721
and I can't
take it anymore.

164
00:07:08,789 --> 00:07:11,925
I had to see you.

165
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:20,350
I don't want any comments
about how messy the place is.

166
00:07:20,434 --> 00:07:21,968
Okay.

167
00:07:22,019 --> 00:07:26,906
And what would clean
look like?

168
00:07:26,974 --> 00:07:29,642
Don't even think
about it.

169
00:07:29,693 --> 00:07:32,311
I can't not think
about it, all right?

170
00:07:32,363 --> 00:07:34,280
It's all I've been able
to think about for two days.

171
00:07:34,331 --> 00:07:36,032
Mike, why are you here?

172
00:07:36,117 --> 00:07:38,618
Because that's not going
to happen.

173
00:07:38,669 --> 00:07:39,986
Now or ever?

174
00:07:40,037 --> 00:07:42,839
You lied to me
about everything.

175
00:07:42,923 --> 00:07:44,174
Rachel--

176
00:07:44,258 --> 00:07:45,208
Do you remember
when I told you I needed time?

177
00:07:45,292 --> 00:07:46,826
That's what
I needed it for--

178
00:07:46,877 --> 00:07:49,429
to process this bomb
that you dropped on me.

179
00:07:49,496 --> 00:07:53,633
I had a nightmare.

180
00:07:53,684 --> 00:07:55,135
You asked why I'm here.
That's why.

181
00:07:55,186 --> 00:07:57,604
I--

182
00:07:57,671 --> 00:07:59,439
you exposed me
to the entire firm.

183
00:07:59,506 --> 00:08:01,307
- I would never do that.
- I know.

184
00:08:01,358 --> 00:08:02,842
And I woke up,
and I realized

185
00:08:02,893 --> 00:08:04,811
that the real nightmare
wouldn't even be that.

186
00:08:04,862 --> 00:08:09,282
The real nightmare
would be--

187
00:08:09,349 --> 00:08:12,986
would be if you didn't want
to be with me.

188
00:08:13,037 --> 00:08:14,320
Do you really
mean that?

189
00:08:14,371 --> 00:08:17,457
I meant it
the first time I ever saw you.

190
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:24,747
Rachel, I know that I'm not
who you want me to be,

191
00:08:24,832 --> 00:08:26,966
but--but you know
what happened in that room.

192
00:08:27,034 --> 00:08:28,218
You know
what we both felt.

193
00:08:28,302 --> 00:08:30,303
I--

194
00:08:30,370 --> 00:08:32,672
I don't want
to lose that.

195
00:08:35,226 --> 00:08:37,310
I just keep wishing
you never told me.

196
00:08:37,377 --> 00:08:40,680
But then it never
would have happened.

197
00:08:40,731 --> 00:08:43,049
And it did.

198
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:44,767
And I'm--

199
00:08:44,852 --> 00:08:46,903
I'm really glad
that it did.

200
00:08:48,355 --> 00:08:52,025
I am too.

201
00:08:52,076 --> 00:08:53,943
But what happens
if you get caught?

202
00:08:54,028 --> 00:08:57,363
Because what you had
may have been a nightmare, Mike,

203
00:08:57,414 --> 00:08:58,531
but you can't tell me
you're not afraid

204
00:08:58,582 --> 00:08:59,532
of being exposed.

205
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:00,833
Of course I am.

206
00:09:00,901 --> 00:09:03,336
But there's nothing
that I can do about it.

207
00:09:03,403 --> 00:09:06,289
Well, maybe there is.

208
00:09:06,373 --> 00:09:08,675
What are you saying?

209
00:09:08,742 --> 00:09:11,294
Quit.

210
00:09:11,378 --> 00:09:13,945
Go in tomorrow,
and just quit.

211
