- No, I will not.

273
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:10,988
Stuck
with these stupid plastic things

274
00:13:11,072 --> 00:13:12,272
that keep breaking.

275
00:13:12,323 --> 00:13:14,074
So buy your own pen.

276
00:13:14,141 --> 00:13:16,777
Bu

277
00:13:16,828 --> 00:13:18,912
okay.

278
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:20,080
There are two things
in this firm

279
00:13:20,147 --> 00:13:22,366
that I hold very sacred--
my uni-balls

280
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:24,117
and my raspberry Bran bars.

281
00:13:24,168 --> 00:13:25,586
And if I have to go
and buy 'em myself,

282
00:13:25,653 --> 00:13:28,255
well, then,
this Barbara L. Tottingham

283
00:13:28,322 --> 00:13:29,840
has a message for me,
loud and clear,

284
00:13:29,924 --> 00:13:31,258
and that's "Louis Litt,
go screw yourself."

285
00:13:31,325 --> 00:13:32,960
Louis, the ink on your face.
You've got just, like--

286
00:13:33,011 --> 00:13:34,294
you've got, like,
a little bit right there.

287
00:13:34,345 --> 00:13:36,129
Where, here?

288
00:13:36,180 --> 00:13:38,465
No, I think you've gotta
give it, like, a good--

289
00:13:38,516 --> 00:13:39,466
Okay, fine.

290
00:13:39,517 --> 00:13:41,935
Gone?

291
00:13:42,003 --> 00:13:44,304
Thank you, Donna.
You're a true friend.

292
00:13:44,355 --> 00:13:45,772
I got your back.

293
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:47,140
Hey, do you remember

294
00:13:47,191 --> 00:13:48,842
when you used to do
those rotator cuff exercises?

295
00:13:48,893 --> 00:13:50,343
Oh, yeah,
what are you kidding? Of course.

296
00:13:50,395 --> 00:13:52,779
Every day for, like, 18 months.
Why do you ask?

297
00:13:52,847 --> 00:13:55,282
No reason.

298
00:13:59,203 --> 00:14:01,204
Edward.

299
00:14:01,289 --> 00:14:02,823
Jessica,
how lovely to see you.

300
00:14:02,874 --> 00:14:04,408
I wanted to thank you.

301
00:14:04,492 --> 00:14:06,910
- Ah. You saw the sign.
- Mm-hmm.

302
00:14:06,995 --> 00:14:08,412
You didn't have
to do that.

303
00:14:08,496 --> 00:14:10,247
Our agreement stipulates
Darby Pearson,

304
00:14:10,331 --> 00:14:11,748
not Pearson Darby.

305
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:16,053
Our agreement also stipulates
a 51/49 percentage structure.

306
00:14:16,137 --> 00:14:17,704
And this is your way
of showing me

307
00:14:17,755 --> 00:14:19,306
that you think of it
as 50/50.

308
00:14:19,373 --> 00:14:21,475
- Merely a gesture.
- Ah.

309
00:14:21,542 --> 00:14:22,759
Heck of a gesture.

310
00:14:22,844 --> 00:14:24,711
How would you propose
to a woman?

311
00:14:24,762 --> 00:14:25,929
A woman?

312
00:14:26,014 --> 00:14:28,598
I think we both know that--
Yes, we do.

313
00:14:28,683 --> 00:14:30,734
Anyway...

314
00:14:30,818 --> 00:14:32,569
It is shaping up
to be a lovely day.

315
00:14:32,654 --> 00:14:33,987
Oh, I wish
I could say that same.

316
00:14:34,055 --> 00:14:35,656
I assume you know
about the latest goings-on

317
00:14:35,723 --> 00:14:37,057
with Hessington Oil.

318
00:14:37,108 --> 00:14:39,076
I wouldn't be much
of a partner if I didn't.

319
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:42,279
Now they've decide to take on
Ava Hessington personally.

320
00:14:42,363 --> 00:14:44,498
- Who is they?
- The U.S. government.

321
00:14:44,565 --> 00:14:46,450
I've decided to let Harvey
handle it.

322
00:14:46,534 --> 00:14:48,669
- Why?
- Why not?

323
00:14:48,736 --> 00:14:49,903
It's not a good time.

324
00:14:49,954 --> 00:14:51,955
He's still digesting
the merger.

325
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,840
- Meaning?
- He's acting out.

326
00:14:53,908 --> 00:14:55,375
Well, he may be
acting out,

327
00:14:55,426 --> 00:14:58,345
but I understand he just got
his client triple the money.

328
00:14:58,412 --> 00:15:01,014
By taking a huge risk
he didn't have to.

329
00:15:01,082 --> 00:15:02,883
This case,
he may have to.

330
00:15:02,934 --> 00:15:05,085
So that's why Harvey.

331
00:15:05,136 --> 00:15:08,305
And this case is more
important to me than just money.

332
00:15:08,389 --> 00:15:10,557
And why is that?

333
00:15:10,608 --> 00:15:13,110
Because it is.

334
00:15:15,429 --> 00:15:16,596
What if I said no?

335
00:15:16,647 --> 00:15:19,265
I'm afraid that's not an option.

336
00:15:19,317 --> 00:15:21,868
So I guess
that sign

337
00:15:21,936 --> 00:15:24,071
really doesn't mean 50/50
after all.

338
00:15:24,122 --> 00:15:26,740
I did say
it was merely a gesture.

339
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:29,876
Hmm.

340
00:15:29,944 --> 00:15:31,912
You keep showing up
to surprise me,

341
00:15:31,963 --> 00:15:33,613
people are gonna
get the wrong idea.

342
00:15:33,664 --> 00:15:36,133
People are going to think
what they're going to think.

343
00:15:36,217 --> 00:15:38,752
I'm here to bury the hatchet.
And what prompted that?

344
00:15:38,803 --> 00:15:41,088
Darby found out what you did
with Deron Williams.

345
00:15:41,139 --> 00:15:42,789
Don't tell me.
He was impressed.

346
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,624
He was pissed.

347
00:15:44,675 --> 00:15:45,792
Thinks you're trying
to get fired.

348
00:15:45,843 --> 00:15:47,677
And you told him
how smart he was.

349
00:15:47,762 --> 00:15:50,013
I told him
you said it wasn't true

350
00:15:50,098 --> 00:15:51,598
and that I believed you,

351
00:15:51,649 --> 00:15:54,267
and then I fought to give you
a chance to prove it.

352
00:15:54,318 --> 00:15:56,636
Ava Hessington.

353
00:15:56,687 --> 00:15:57,637
I got you on it.

354
00:15:57,688 --> 00:15:58,805
What does that matter
to me?

355
00:15:58,856 --> 00:15:59,906
Harvey,

356
00:15:59,974 --> 00:16:02,308
I know you and I
have had our problems,

357
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,361
but this is a chance
for us to move past it.

358
00:16:04,445 --> 00:16:05,612
Let's take it.

359
00:16:05,663 --> 00:16:07,531
You really do
wanna make up.

360
00:16:07,615 --> 00:16:09,533
I never wanted to be at odds
in the first place.

361
00:16:09,617 --> 00:16:13,286
Neither did I.

362
00:16:13,337 --> 00:16:15,589
Are we good?

363
00:16:15,656 --> 00:16:18,208
Don't you wanna tell me
I better win this goddamn case?

364
00:16:18,292 --> 00:16:19,993
I didn't think
I had to.

365
00:16:20,044 --> 00:16:21,605
Never stopped you
from saying it before.

366
00:16:21,629 --> 00:16:24,548
Well, I'm learning
to let go.

367
00:16:25,683 --> 00:16:27,884
Oh, Harvey,
there is one more thing.

368
00:16:27,969 --> 00:16:31,638
You better win
this goddamn case.

369
00:16:51,409 --> 00:16:53,026
I know
it's not my place,

370
00:16:53,077 --> 00:16:56,046
but you really suck
at quitting.

371
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:57,197
I can explain.

372
00:16:57,248 --> 00:17:00,634
No need.
It was just a suggestion.

373
00:17:00,701 --> 00:17:01,968
Rachel, I tried to do it,
but--

374
00:17:02,036 --> 00:17:05,371
But then Jessica
gave you this office to stay?

375
00:17:05,423 --> 00:17:06,873
Actually,
she gave me this office

376
00:17:06,924 --> 00:17:11,011
before I could even
bring it up.

377
00:17:11,062 --> 00:17:12,095
Well, aren't you

378
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:13,346
just the luckiest person
in the world?

379
00:17:13,397 --> 00:17:14,714
Rachel--

380
00:17:14,765 --> 00:17:16,566
You came to me,
you were petrified

381
00:17:16,651 --> 00:17:18,551
of being exposed,
and I gave you a way out.

382
00:17:18,603 --> 00:17:22,022
And now, 12 hours later,
you're in a brand-new office

383
00:17:22,073 --> 00:17:23,323
with a diploma on the wall
that, for all I know,

384
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:24,658
came from Kinko's.

385
00:17:24,725 --> 00:17:26,860
What do you want me to do?
Everyone hangs one.

386
00:17:26,911 --> 00:17:31,231
No, Mike,
everyone doesn't just hang one.

387
00:17:31,282 --> 00:17:32,699
So that's
what this is really about.

388
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:34,734
You're damn right
it is.

389
00:17:34,785 --> 00:17:38,622
I've been trying to earn one
for as long as I can remember.

390
00:17:38,706 --> 00:17:41,174
And you have one and everything
that goes with it,

391
00:17:41,242 --> 00:17:43,677
and you didn't do
a single thing to deserve it.

392
00:17:43,744 --> 00:17:44,794
You have no idea
what I have or haven't done

393
00:17:44,879 --> 00:17:46,379
to get where I am.

394
00:17:46,430 --> 00:17:48,715
And that's
the whole problem.

395
00:17:48,766 --> 00:17:51,184
I have no idea
who you are.

396
00:18:26,094 --> 00:18:29,764
Harvey, I'm just in the middle
of a little afternoon crossword.

397
00:18:29,815 --> 00:18:30,932
Are you a puzzler?

398
00:18:30,983 --> 00:18:32,567
Don't you have work
to do?

399
00:18:32,634 --> 00:18:34,134
My dear fellow,
if I have to do work,

400
00:18:34,186 --> 00:18:36,103
then I'm not doing my job.

401
00:18:36,155 --> 00:18:37,104
What can I do
for you?

402
00:18:37,156 --> 00:18:38,489
Jessica told me

403
00:18:38,574 --> 00:18:40,358
that you agreed to let me
be lead on Ava Hessington.

404
00:18:40,442 --> 00:18:41,742
I wanted to thank you.

405
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:44,144
- You're welcome.
- There's just one problem.

406
00:18:44,196 --> 00:18:46,914
You didn't agree to anything.
You demanded it.

407
00:18:46,982 --> 00:18:48,783
And you let Jessica
play good cop

408
00:18:48,834 --> 00:18:51,169
because you didn't wanna
undermine the chain of command.

409
00:18:51,253 --> 00:18:53,120
That's quite
the conspiracy theory.

410
00:18:53,172 --> 00:18:54,655
Well,
here's the good news.

411
00:18:54,706 --> 00:18:56,657
My plate's a little full
right now.

412
00:18:56,708 --> 00:18:59,460
And since you didn't want me
on this case in the first place,

413
00:18:59,511 --> 00:19:01,328
why don't you let
somebody else handle it?

414
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:03,431
Good luck.
I hear it's a tough one.

415
00:19:03,498 --> 00:19:06,333
What do you want?

416
00:19:06,385 --> 00:19:08,102
I want out.

417
00:19:08,169 --> 00:19:09,270
I win this,

418
00:19:09,337 --> 00:19:11,639
you tear up my noncompete,
and you fire me.

419
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:14,008
You hate this merger
that much.

420
00:19:14,059 --> 00:19:15,676
I had an agreement
with Jessica,

421
00:19:15,727 --> 00:19:16,944
and I honored it.

422
00:19:17,012 --> 00:19:19,680
Then she accused me
of trying to get fired.

423
00:19:19,731 --> 00:19:21,199
Then she lied to me

424
00:19:21,283 --> 00:19:22,817
by claiming
that she fought for me

425
00:19:22,868 --> 00:19:24,151
to be on this case.

426
00:19:24,203 --> 00:19:27,371
She really does wanna
make up with you, you know.

427
00:19:27,456 --> 00:19:29,040
Funny way
of showing it.

428
00:19:29,124 --> 00:19:30,491
Ironic.

429
00:19:30,542 --> 00:19:32,577
Her belief that you wanted
to be fired

430
00:19:32,661 --> 00:19:35,079
led you to wanting
to be fired.

431
00:19:35,163 --> 00:19:37,999
Do we have
a deal or not?

432
00:19:38,050 --> 00:19:42,386
It appears we do.

433
00:19:49,428 --> 00:19:52,179
Oh, hey.
Uh, go ahead.

434
00:19:52,231 --> 00:19:54,348
No, that's all right.
You were here first.

435
00:19:54,399 --> 00:19:55,716
Why are you being
so polite?

436
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:56,984
Come on, you have
one stupid copy.

437
00:19:57,052 --> 00:19:58,436
You could've finished it
already.

438
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:00,938
Louis, I--

439
00:20:01,023 --> 00:20:04,075
A letter of resignation?

440
00:20:04,159 --> 00:20:05,109
Why?

441
00:20:05,193 --> 00:20:07,111
It's complicated.

442
00:20:07,195 --> 00:20:10,665
Well, simplify it for me,
Mike.

443
00:20:12,668 --> 00:20:14,201
Harvey.

444
00:20:14,253 --> 00:20:15,536
He's the one
who hired me.

445
00:20:15,587 --> 00:20:17,071
Now he wants nothing
to do with me.

446
00:20:17,122 --> 00:20:18,405
What are you talking about?
He just gave you a new office.

447
00:20:18,457 --> 00:20:20,041
No, Jessica gave me
a new office.

448
00:20:20,092 --> 00:20:24,912
If it was up to Harvey,
I wouldn't even have a cubicle.

449
00:20:24,963 --> 00:20:27,715
What happened?

450
00:20:27,766 --> 00:20:31,085
All that matters is that,
uh, I can't fix it.

451
00:20:33,689 --> 00:20:34,939
You know, when we were
in the bullpen,

452
00:20:35,023 --> 00:20:37,942
Harvey was like Superman.

453
00:20:38,026 --> 00:20:39,894
And then, one day,

454
00:20:39,945 --> 00:20:41,896
Hardman decided to just
knock him down a peg.

455
00:20:41,947 --> 00:20:43,531
Gave him
this bullshit assignment,

456
00:20:43,598 --> 00:20:45,399
undoable workload,
unwinnable case.

457
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:47,034
And I took it
as a chance

458
00:20:47,102 --> 00:20:49,453
to break down his walls
and offer my help.

459
00:20:49,538 --> 00:20:50,738
And I just thought,
this just might be

460
00:20:50,789 --> 00:20:52,106
the chance
that we could become--

461
00:20:52,157 --> 00:20:54,792
- Friends.
- Yeah.

462
00:20:54,876 --> 00:20:58,329
And he looked at me--
how dare I?

463
00:20:58,413 --> 00:20:59,830
I get it.
He's alone.

464
00:20:59,915 --> 00:21:01,465
He always has been.
He always will be.

465
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:03,501
Always was.

466
00:21:03,585 --> 00:21:06,220
Harvey is
not Superman anymore.

467
00:21:07,806 --> 00:21:11,425
He's Batman.

468
00:21:11,476 --> 00:21:13,311
And Batman needs Robin.

469
00:21:13,395 --> 00:21:15,629
And I just need
to remind him of that.

470
00:21:15,681 --> 00:21:17,264
What's the one thing
that Harvey values

471
00:21:17,316 --> 00:21:18,432
over everything else?

472
00:21:18,483 --> 00:21:19,567
- Winning.
- Yeah.

473
00:21:19,634 --> 00:21:20,768
You help him win,

474
00:21:20,819 --> 00:21:22,803
he'll remember
why he needs you.

475
00:21:22,854 --> 00:21:24,905
I have to figure out
what cases he's working on.

476
00:21:24,973 --> 00:21:26,407
The I.T. Department
has access to every computer

477
00:21:26,474 --> 00:21:28,743
in the entire firm,
syncs up every night.

478
00:21:28,810 --> 00:21:31,245
So all I have to do is get
access to Harvey's hard drive.

479
00:21:31,312 --> 00:21:33,313
That place is a fortress.

480
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:37,535
Benjamin.

481
00:21:39,254 --> 00:21:40,705
It's you.

482
00:21:40,789 --> 00:21:42,423
Aw, that's sweet.
You remember me.

483
00:21:42,490 --> 00:21:43,657
Oh, yes.

484
00:21:43,709 --> 00:21:45,659
I remember everyone
who's ever bamboozled me

485
00:21:45,711 --> 00:21:47,494
into giving them
a top-of-the-line laptop.

486
00:21:47,546 --> 00:21:48,996
Their names
are Michael Ross.

487
00:21:49,047 --> 00:21:51,015
I didn't bamboozle you,
Benjamin.

488
00:21:51,099 --> 00:21:52,499
I won it
fair and square.

489
00:21:52,551 --> 00:21:55,019
And I've been tracking
every Internet move you've made

490
00:21:55,103 --> 00:21:58,022
for the past ten months,
waiting for the slipup.

491
00:21:58,106 --> 00:22:00,608
Bet you thought you had me
at teenybikini.com.

492
00:22:00,675 --> 00:22:02,560
No.
No, no.

493
00:22:02,644 --> 00:22:04,061
Because I cross-referenced that

494
00:22:04,146 --> 00:22:06,847
with your workplace
harassment case, and I knew.

495
00:22:06,898 --> 00:22:08,816
But don't think I'm not aware
that you went home for dinner

496
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:11,318
and used your personal computer
to go back there.

497
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:13,287
Okay,
that's not actionable,

498
00:22:13,354 --> 00:22:15,373
but hacking
my personal computer is.

499
00:22:15,457 --> 00:22:18,209
Good luck proving that.
Now, what do you want?

500
00:22:18,293 --> 00:22:20,194
- I want access to a hard drive.
- No way.

501
00:22:20,245 --> 00:22:21,545
Not only that,
I want you to give me

502
00:22:21,630 --> 00:22:23,381
whatever I want
whenever I want it

503
00:22:23,465 --> 00:22:24,548
for the rest
of your life.

504
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:25,916
And why would I
do that?

505
00:22:26,001 --> 00:22:27,385
Oh, right.

506
00:22:27,469 --> 00:22:30,871
Because I just recorded you
admitting to violating the law.

507
00:22:30,922 --> 00:22:33,974
- The XJS-5000.
- Mm-hmm.

508
00:22:34,042 --> 00:22:35,593
- You--you set me up.
- Yep.

509
00:22:35,677 --> 00:22:37,645
You knew that I would
track your home computer.

510
00:22:37,712 --> 00:22:39,146
And after
you've been convicted,

511
00:22:39,214 --> 00:22:42,650
you'll be lucky to be hired
as a network administrator...

512
00:22:42,717 --> 00:22:44,902
