00:32:11,591 --> 00:32:14,259
Do you want a replay?
'Cause I will go right now.

767
00:32:14,310 --> 00:32:16,728
- Like you could.
- I could!

768
00:32:16,796 --> 00:32:19,014
Soon...ish.

769
00:32:19,098 --> 00:32:20,799
Do you have, like,
an energy drink or something?

770
00:32:20,850 --> 00:32:22,901
- Oh.
- Come on! We were up all night.

771
00:32:22,969 --> 00:32:24,302
You kept me up
all night.

772
00:32:24,354 --> 00:32:27,305
<i>You</i> kept me up all night.

773
00:32:36,649 --> 00:32:39,668
I can't tell you
how it feels

774
00:32:39,752 --> 00:32:41,486
that you know.

775
00:32:41,537 --> 00:32:43,488
Mm, well, who knew

776
00:32:43,539 --> 00:32:46,258
that honesty
was the best policy?

777
00:32:46,325 --> 00:32:49,378
Oh, wait.
Everyone knew that.

778
00:32:51,881 --> 00:32:54,349
What?

779
00:33:01,691 --> 00:33:03,976
Can I help you?

780
00:33:06,279 --> 00:33:07,195
Louis Litt.

781
00:33:07,280 --> 00:33:08,814
Oh, I know
who you are.

782
00:33:08,865 --> 00:33:11,233
Freshly minted
senior partner,

783
00:33:11,317 --> 00:33:13,535
expert in matters
of corporate finance,

784
00:33:13,619 --> 00:33:16,021
and the man responsible
for the superb training

785
00:33:16,072 --> 00:33:17,155
of the associates.

786
00:33:18,992 --> 00:33:21,076
You've looked into me.
Mmhmm.

787
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:24,079
I've looked into you.

788
00:33:24,163 --> 00:33:25,998
Tarte au chocolat
from Cafe Pouchkine.

789
00:33:26,049 --> 00:33:28,366
The best patisserie
in Paris.

790
00:33:28,418 --> 00:33:30,085
A steeping cup
of da Hong pao.

791
00:33:30,169 --> 00:33:32,170
The most expensive tea
in the world.

792
00:33:32,221 --> 00:33:34,172
Two of my favorite things.

793
00:33:34,223 --> 00:33:37,843
What better to enjoy
after signing this order...

794
00:33:37,894 --> 00:33:39,144
Making me quartermaster?

795
00:33:39,211 --> 00:33:40,512
Pity you don't have
a Montblanc pen

796
00:33:40,563 --> 00:33:41,763
for me to sign it with.

797
00:33:41,848 --> 00:33:44,566
With cobalt ink.

798
00:33:44,650 --> 00:33:46,184
We already have
a quartermaster.

799
00:33:46,235 --> 00:33:47,652
Sir, I know...

800
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,771
That this is
Nigel's position

801
00:33:49,856 --> 00:33:52,107
and him losing it
would not be easy for him.

802
00:33:52,191 --> 00:33:53,909
But let me
just assure you,

803
00:33:53,993 --> 00:33:56,912
I'm not just prepared
for this position...

804
00:33:56,996 --> 00:33:59,364
I was born for it.

805
00:33:59,415 --> 00:34:02,367
I have PhDs
in chemical engineering

806
00:34:02,418 --> 00:34:03,919
and petroleum exploration.

807
00:34:04,003 --> 00:34:06,588
I've made it to the top
in a field dominated by men,

808
00:34:06,672 --> 00:34:09,041
and I'm facing
a prison sentence

809
00:34:09,092 --> 00:34:11,209
for an allegation
which any man in my position

810
00:34:11,260 --> 00:34:12,577
would be fined for.

811
00:34:12,628 --> 00:34:14,713
Every similar case
has been settled with a fine,

812
00:34:14,764 --> 00:34:15,931
not prison.

813
00:34:16,015 --> 00:34:17,136
That's what we're proposing.

814
00:34:17,183 --> 00:34:19,217
Well, there's just
one problem.

815
00:34:19,268 --> 00:34:21,686
I'm not charging you
because you're a woman.

816
00:34:21,754 --> 00:34:23,271
I'm charging you
because you're the one I caught.

817
00:34:23,356 --> 00:34:25,807
Ava, can you give us
a minute?

818
00:34:34,283 --> 00:34:36,735
Okay, she's gonna
write you a check.

819
00:34:36,786 --> 00:34:38,070
Let's talk about how much.

820
00:34:38,121 --> 00:34:40,288
I'm sorry, Harvey.

821
00:34:40,373 --> 00:34:42,324
Not this time.

822
00:34:44,744 --> 00:34:45,944
Is that what I said to you
on Hazelton?

823
00:34:45,995 --> 00:34:47,662
That was
a long time ago.

824
00:34:47,747 --> 00:34:49,915
We're not at the D.A.'s office
anymore.

825
00:34:49,966 --> 00:34:52,784
I didn't realize our bond
had an expiration date.

826
00:34:52,835 --> 00:34:54,619
It doesn't, but...

827
00:34:54,670 --> 00:34:57,889
you want to deal on this,
I need jail time.

828
00:34:59,842 --> 00:35:01,093
You're running for office?

829
00:35:01,144 --> 00:35:02,561
What if I am?

830
00:35:02,628 --> 00:35:05,230
You need a scalp.

831
00:35:05,297 --> 00:35:06,731
I can think of four people
off the top of my head

832
00:35:06,799 --> 00:35:08,279
that make her look like
Mother Teresa.

833
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:10,519
Harvey, I can't afford
to horse trade on this.

834
00:35:10,603 --> 00:35:11,603
You've done it before.

835
00:35:11,654 --> 00:35:13,605
And I'll do it again,
but...not today.

836
00:35:13,656 --> 00:35:16,358
Richard, you are singling out
this woman, and it's wrong.

837
00:35:17,660 --> 00:35:18,944
That's not my problem.

838
00:35:18,995 --> 00:35:20,362
What if I told you
I need this one?

839
00:35:20,446 --> 00:35:24,082
Then I'd have to tell you...
I'm sorry.

840
00:35:25,668 --> 00:35:27,202
Not gonna forget this.

841
00:35:27,286 --> 00:35:28,620
Harvey, look.

842
00:35:28,671 --> 00:35:31,256
If our bond can't survive
me telling you no,

843
00:35:31,323 --> 00:35:32,991
then...

844
00:35:33,042 --> 00:35:35,961
It didn't mean much
to begin with.

845
00:35:44,003 --> 00:35:47,305
- Hey, Rach.
- No time, code two!

846
00:35:47,356 --> 00:35:48,690
Richard Gere's
in the lobby?

847
00:35:48,774 --> 00:35:51,193
- Leaving now, let's go.
- Relax.

848
00:35:51,277 --> 00:35:54,196
We have trained for this.
Okay.

849
00:35:55,731 --> 00:35:57,682
Wait!

850
00:36:11,664 --> 00:36:13,865
Congratulations.

851
00:36:13,916 --> 00:36:17,368
Your writing implements
and nourishment of choice.

852
00:36:17,420 --> 00:36:18,553
Mm.

853
00:36:18,638 --> 00:36:22,557
Yeah, I'd say I'm sorry,
but I'm not.

854
00:36:22,642 --> 00:36:24,809
Please don't do this.

855
00:36:24,877 --> 00:36:26,895
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

856
00:36:26,979 --> 00:36:29,397
You're not gonna trick me into
letting you stay quartermaster

857
00:36:29,482 --> 00:36:30,932
just so you can take away
what's most dear to me

858
00:36:31,017 --> 00:36:33,401
little by little.

859
00:36:33,486 --> 00:36:37,105
Then I'm afraid I'm gonna have
to take it away all at once.

860
00:36:38,574 --> 00:36:39,991
What are you
talking about?

861
00:36:40,059 --> 00:36:42,861
I took you for a bylaws man.
It seems I was wrong.

862
00:36:42,912 --> 00:36:44,395
At Darby International,

863
00:36:44,447 --> 00:36:45,947
one cannot be in charge
of both the animate

864
00:36:46,032 --> 00:36:48,533
and the inanimate
at the same time.

865
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:53,955
Your beloved associates
are mine.

866
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,290
You set me up.

867
00:36:55,374 --> 00:36:56,708
What better way
to catch a rat

868
00:36:56,759 --> 00:36:58,460
than with
quartermaster cheese?

869
00:36:58,544 --> 00:36:59,761
What are you gonna do,

870
00:36:59,845 --> 00:37:02,881
beg Darby to undo
what you just begged him to do?

871
00:37:05,101 --> 00:37:07,686
Hold on.

872
00:37:07,753 --> 00:37:11,056
Nigel, the associates
are my life.

873
00:37:13,109 --> 00:37:14,425
So please don't do this.

874
00:37:14,477 --> 00:37:16,478
When I was
at preparatory school,

875
00:37:16,562 --> 00:37:19,231
like you,
I was bullied again and again.

876
00:37:19,282 --> 00:37:22,067
It was painful,
but I always saw them coming.

877
00:37:22,118 --> 00:37:23,601
But with you,
I didn't.

878
00:37:23,653 --> 00:37:26,988
So it wasn't a stab in the back,
it was a stab in the heart.

879
00:37:27,073 --> 00:37:29,741
And I just gave you
the opportunity to take it back,

880
00:37:29,792 --> 00:37:31,376
and you passed.

881
00:37:31,443 --> 00:37:35,664
So no, quartermaster Litt,
I won't forgive you.

882
00:37:41,304 --> 00:37:42,954
Nice office.

883
00:37:43,005 --> 00:37:44,723
Thanks.

884
00:37:44,790 --> 00:37:47,008
Do you mind
if I ask you a favor?

885
00:37:47,093 --> 00:37:48,176
Yeah, anything.

886
00:37:48,261 --> 00:37:49,978
I have
a ton of old files

887
00:37:50,062 --> 00:37:51,930
that I need organized
and shipped to storage,

888
00:37:51,981 --> 00:37:55,133
and I was wondering if you
could maybe do that for me.

889
00:37:55,184 --> 00:37:56,634
I

890
00:37:56,686 --> 00:37:58,153
Because I figured if you were
suddenly doing things for people

891
00:37:58,237 --> 00:38:00,105
that they don't need you to do,
didn't ask you to do,

892
00:38:00,156 --> 00:38:03,775
and don't want you to do,
then maybe I'd get in on that.

893
00:38:06,579 --> 00:38:09,748
I put that on Harvey's desk
for him, not you.

894
00:38:09,815 --> 00:38:12,033
Maybe.

895
00:38:12,118 --> 00:38:13,818
But I know
what you don't seem to get.

896
00:38:13,869 --> 00:38:16,654
Harvey didn't value you
for your help on cases.

897
00:38:16,706 --> 00:38:19,157
He valued you for your loyalty,
which he told you last night.

898
00:38:19,208 --> 00:38:20,375
Yeah, I know that.

899
00:38:20,459 --> 00:38:21,619
And I'm trying
to get it back,

900
00:38:21,627 --> 00:38:22,827
and this is
the only way I know how.

901
00:38:22,878 --> 00:38:24,162
By sending Rachel
to distract me

902
00:38:24,213 --> 00:38:25,630
and sneaking
into his office?

903
00:38:25,681 --> 00:38:27,299
Oh, by the way, you think
I don't know about you two?

904
00:38:27,350 --> 00:38:29,000
Took me one look.
Donna, come on.

905
00:38:29,051 --> 00:38:32,020
You wanna know how
to get Harvey's loyalty back?

906
00:38:32,104 --> 00:38:34,522
Get in a time machine and undo
what you did with Jessica.

907
00:38:34,607 --> 00:38:36,507
Oh, shoot,
you can't do that.

908
00:38:36,559 --> 00:38:39,110
You know what, I figured
you'd bring this file back.

909
00:38:39,178 --> 00:38:41,146
There's also one
in your bottom drawer.

910
00:38:41,197 --> 00:38:44,816
You might wanna grab that too.

911
00:38:44,867 --> 00:38:45,984
And just in case of that,

912
00:38:46,035 --> 00:38:48,737
I put seven other copies
in his office.

913
00:38:48,821 --> 00:38:50,288
'Cause whether
he forgives me or not,

914
00:38:50,356 --> 00:38:52,824
he's still gonna need it.

915
00:38:52,875 --> 00:38:55,160
Some random associate
gave him all that information

916
00:38:55,211 --> 00:38:57,712
on Ava Hessington?

917
00:38:57,797 --> 00:38:58,747
No way.

918
00:38:58,831 --> 00:39:01,299
It was Scottie.

919
00:39:01,367 --> 00:39:03,534
Yeah, I found the ticket
to Trinidad-Tobago.

920
00:39:03,586 --> 00:39:04,803
It's not a giant leap.

921
00:39:04,870 --> 00:39:07,505
The only problem is
Scottie's not here.

922
00:39:07,556 --> 00:39:08,923
She's in London.

923
00:39:09,008 --> 00:39:11,542
And Harvey--
he is still gonna need this.

924
00:39:11,594 --> 00:39:15,597
This file doesn't lead
to Harvey forgiving you.

925
00:39:15,681 --> 00:39:17,098
Donna...

926
00:39:17,183 --> 00:39:19,067
Please could you just separate
our relationship

927
00:39:19,151 --> 00:39:20,952
from yours and his
for just, like, one second?

928
00:39:20,986 --> 00:39:22,354
Are you kidding me?

929
00:39:22,405 --> 00:39:24,022
Do you think I'm mad
just because of him?

930
00:39:24,073 --> 00:39:25,990
You did this
to me too.

931
00:39:26,058 --> 00:39:27,525
And whether you appreciate it
or not,

932
00:39:27,576 --> 00:39:29,277
I've had your back
since the day that you got here.

933
00:39:29,362 --> 00:39:31,863
Yes. Yes, you have.
But what about last year?

934
00:39:31,914 --> 00:39:33,248
When I had your back,
you ignored me,

935
00:39:33,332 --> 00:39:34,999
and it almost cost him
his license.

936
00:39:35,067 --> 00:39:37,669
The difference is
I did what I did for him,

937
00:39:37,736 --> 00:39:39,254
not for me.

938
00:39:39,338 --> 00:39:41,406
And I didn't get
a brand-new office for it.

939
00:39:41,457 --> 00:39:43,675
I got fired.

940
00:39:53,679 --> 00:39:54,896
Yum.

941
00:39:54,964 --> 00:39:57,099
Oh, what do you want, Michael?
Please.

942
00:39:57,150 --> 00:39:58,633
I'm just trying to eat
my egg McMuffin

943
00:39:58,684 --> 00:39:59,935
while I'm still off-line,
okay?

944
00:39:59,986 --> 00:40:02,654
I thought
you were never off-line.

945
00:40:02,739 --> 00:40:05,690
Five minutes a day.

946
00:40:05,775 --> 00:40:07,192
Listen, Benjamin,

947
00:40:07,276 --> 00:40:09,945
I don't wanna hold what's
on this dictaphone over you

948
00:40:09,996 --> 00:40:11,113
for the rest
of your life.

949
00:40:11,164 --> 00:40:13,532
Why not?

950
00:40:13,616 --> 00:40:15,117
I don't need
any more enemies.

951
00:40:15,168 --> 00:40:17,452
I'd rather have a friend,
but...

952
00:40:17,503 --> 00:40:19,421
I do need a favor.

953
00:40:19,488 --> 00:40:21,123
And if I don't
give it to you,

954
00:40:21,174 --> 00:40:25,127
then what do you do
with the dictaphone?

955
00:40:25,178 --> 00:40:26,762
It's the only copy
there is.

956
00:40:26,829 --> 00:40:27,963
Go on, erase it.

957
00:40:28,014 --> 00:40:30,048
Then I'll ask you
my favor.

958
00:40:30,133 --> 00:40:32,934
How do I know
that this is the only copy?

959
00:40:33,002 --> 00:40:35,387
Because I'm giving you
my word.

960
00:40:40,643 --> 00:40:41,726
What do you need?

961
00:40:41,811 --> 00:40:45,981
I need you to build me
a time machine.

962
00:40:47,116 --> 00:40:49,401
And a bite
of the sandwich.

963
00:40:49,485 --> 00:40:52,020
Come on.
That's not sanitary, Michael.

964
00:40:52,071 --> 00:40:54,873
Come on,
just a little.

965
00:40:54,957 --> 00:40:57,793
You can have
the rest.

966
00:40:59,745 --> 00:41:01,529
- How did it go with Richard?
- It didn't.

967
00:41:01,581 --> 00:41:03,364
He didn't budge.
Why not?

968
00:41:03,416 --> 00:41:05,700
Says he's running for office,
but it doesn't make sense.

969
00:41:05,751 --> 00:41:08,503
Yeah, it does.

970
00:41:10,539 --> 00:41:12,207
Son of bitch!

971
00:41:12,258 --> 00:41:13,374
He looks me in the eye,

972
00:41:13,426 --> 00:41:14,826
and he feeds me
a bullshit sandwich.

973
00:41:14,877 --> 00:41:16,878
He's obviously not
the same man he used to be.

974
00:41:16,929 --> 00:41:19,147
Yeah, well, I am.

975
00:41:19,215 --> 00:41:21,183
Wait a second.
Let me guess. Mike?

976
00:41:21,234 --> 00:41:22,434
Just because you use it

977
00:41:22,518 --> 00:41:23,551
doesn't mean you have
to forgive him.

978
00:41:23,603 --> 00:41:25,553
You're right.
I don't.

979
00:41:33,663 --> 00:41:35,897
Harvey.
What are you doing here?

980
00:41:35,948 --> 00:41:38,233
Hessington Oil's
number one competitor

981
00:41:38,284 --> 00:41:41,169
also happens to be your biggest
campaign contributor?

982
00:41:41,237 --> 00:41:42,454
Which has nothing to do
with the fact

983
00:41:42,538 --> 00:41:43,622
that your client
broke the law.

984
00:41:43,706 --> 00:41:44,906
You don't want a deal.

985
00:41:44,957 --> 00:41:47,008
What you want
is a long, drawn-out trial

986
00:41:47,076 --> 00:41:49,010
that puts our stock
in the toilet.

987
00:41:49,078 --> 00:41:51,213
You think I wasn't
gonna find that out?

988
00:41:51,264 --> 00:41:52,597
I mean,
I gotta hand it to you.

989
00:41:52,682 --> 00:41:53,748
You set it up perfectly

990
00:41:53,799 --> 00:41:55,016
to shield yourself
from prosecution.

991
00:41:55,084 --> 00:41:57,853
To shield myself
from breaking the law.

992
00:41:57,920 --> 00:42:00,272
Prosecuting the competition.

993
00:42:00,356 --> 00:42:02,023
It's a hell
of a campaign slogan.

994
00:42:02,091 --> 00:42:04,976
Harvey,
your client did this.

995
00:42:05,061 --> 00:42:06,928
I'm not going
after an innocent person.

996
00:42:06,979 --> 00:42:08,780
And you know
that if I win this election,

997
00:42:08,865 --> 00:42:10,315
I will do good things.

998
00:42:10,399 --> 00:42:12,534
You know what, you sound
just like Cameron Dennis.

999
00:42:12,601 --> 00:42:13,818
You remember?

1000
00:42:13,903 --> 00:42:16,204
Always a reason,
always out for the greater good.

1001
00:42:16,272 --> 00:42:18,490
But in the end,
it's all about him.

1002
00:42:18,574 --> 00:42:20,659
Look, I've never claimed
to be out for the greater good.

1003
00:42:20,743 --> 00:42:23,578
So cut me a deal
and find yourself another donor.

1004
00:42:23,629 --> 00:42:26,748
Harvey, it's too late.

1005
00:42:26,799 --> 00:42:29,384
Please.
I need this.

1006
00:42:30,619 --> 00:42:34,339
Well, that's not
my problem.

1007
00:42:35,457 --> 00:42:38,310
Send Carolyn my love.

1008
00:42:41,814 --> 00:42:43,148
You wanted to see me?

1009
00:42:43,232 --> 00:42:46,017
I know why you care so much
about Ava Hessington.

1010
00:42:46,102 --> 00:42:47,068
Well, it's no secret.

1011
00:42:47,136 --> 00:42:48,737
Her father
was my first client.

1012
00:42:48,804 --> 00:42:53,408
I think he was
a little bit more than that.

1013
00:42:53,475 --> 00:42:54,976
It was a different time.

1014
00:42:55,027 --> 00:42:57,362
Does she know?

1015
00:42:57,446 --> 00:42:59,998
She knows
that I care about her.

1016
00:43:00,082 --> 00:43:01,923
I'm sorry, was there
something else you wanted?

1017
00:43:01,951 --> 00:43:03,168
Just to let you know
that if I could figure that out,

1018
00:43:03,252 --> 00:43:04,869
Harvey can figure that out.

1019
00:43:04,954 --> 00:43:06,621
And why would that
be a problem?

1020
00:43:06,672 --> 00:43:08,123
Because it's one thing
for Harvey to know

1021
00:43:08,174 --> 00:43:09,624
that this case
is important to you,

1022
00:43:09,675 --> 00:43:12,928
another to know
how important.

1023
00:43:12,995 --> 00:43:15,513
Are you telling me
you don't trust him?

1024
00:43:15,598 --> 00:43:16,932
I told you

1025
00:43:16,999 --> 00:43:20,168
he's having a difficult time
digesting this merger.

1026
00:43:20,219 --> 00:43:24,806
I don't want him using this
as leverage to leave.

1027
00:43:24,857 --> 00:43:26,608
At the end of the day,

1028
00:43:26,675 --> 00:43:29,945
I don't believe
Harvey really wants to leave.

1029
00:43:31,447 --> 00:43:32,614
Harvey...

1030
00:43:32,681 --> 00:43:33,898
What a coincidence.

1031
00:43:33,983 --> 00:43:36,851
Cameron.
You grew the mustache back.

1032
00:43:36,902 --> 00:43:38,737
I'll let you in
on a little secret.

1033
00:43:38,821 --> 00:43:41,539
It wasn't a success
the first time.

1034
00:43:41,624 --> 00:43:43,024
What are you doing here?

1035
00:43:43,075 --> 00:43:44,793
Ah, Richard told me
that you mentioned me

1036
00:43:44,860 --> 00:43:46,294
at your last meeting.

1037
00:43:46,362 --> 00:43:49,130
It's funny,
'cause he called me

1038
00:43:49,198 --> 00:43:51,699
after your first meeting,
wanted my advice.

1039
00:43:51,751 --> 00:43:53,501
So I guess
you're here to tell me

1040
00:43:53,552 --> 00:43:55,170
he's not gonna give me
a deal.

1041
00:43:55,221 --> 00:43:57,205
I'm here to tell you he's
recusing himself from the case.

1042
00:43:57,256 --> 00:43:59,174
He didn't want the appearance
of a conflict

1043
00:43:59,225 --> 00:44:01,259
to damage the workings
of justice.

1044
00:44:01,344 --> 00:44:03,211
So he appointed
a special prosecutor.

1045
00:44:03,262 --> 00:44:06,047
Lucky for me,
I've always been special.

1046
00:44:06,098 --> 00:44:07,732
No, you've always been
a corrupt prick.

1047
00:44:07,817 --> 00:44:09,517
It just took me a while
to realize it.

1048
00:44:09,568 --> 00:44:11,052
And it took me a while
to realize

1049
00:44:11,103 --> 00:44:13,355
that you don't have a speck
of loyalty in your entire body.

1050
00:44:13,406 --> 00:44:16,324
Loyalty is a two-way street,
and you ran me off the road.

1051
00:44:16,392 --> 00:44:18,243
So what
are you gonna do?

1052
00:44:18,327 --> 00:44:20,412
You gonna let Jessica fight your
fight like you did last time,

1053
00:44:20,496 --> 00:44:21,729
or you gonna run away

1054
00:44:21,781 --> 00:44:23,031
like you did when you left
the D.A.'s office?

1055
00:44:23,082 --> 00:44:25,033
Neither one, Cameron.
But thank you.

1056
00:44:25,084 --> 00:44:26,701
For what?

1057
00:44:26,752 --> 00:44:29,737
For reminding me
that I don't run from a fight.

1058
00:44:32,741 --> 00:44:33,708
What was so important
that I had

1059
00:44:33,759 --> 00:44:35,627
to come down here
right away?

1060
00:44:35,711 --> 00:44:38,847
Don't tell me
you want a bigger office.

1061
00:44:38,914 --> 00:44:40,682
You told me
that I can think of this office

1062
00:44:40,749 --> 00:44:43,134
as a reminder
of what I did to Harvey

1063
00:44:43,219 --> 00:44:46,638
or as a symbol
of what I can do at this firm.

1064
00:44:46,722 --> 00:44:48,890
But the thing is
I don't wanna be here

1065
00:44:48,941 --> 00:44:50,925
if I'm not solid
with Harvey.

1066
00:44:50,976 --> 00:44:53,428
Well,
that's between you and Harvey.

1067
00:44:53,479 --> 00:44:57,399
It's between you and me.

1068
00:44:57,450 --> 00:45:00,235
You put yourself between us
when you blackmailed me.

1069
00:45:00,286 --> 00:45:02,153
Well, the word
you're looking for is extortion,

1070
00:45:02,238 --> 00:45:03,655
not blackmail,

1071
00:45:03,739 --> 00:45:06,157
and I'm not going to comment
on that accusation.

1072
00:45:06,242 --> 00:45:09,077
But as for your choices,

1073
00:45:09,128 --> 00:45:11,112
you made those
all by yourself.

1074
00:45:11,163 --> 00:45:12,414
So don't come crying
to me.

1075
00:45:14,417 --> 00:45:16,951
This is a copy of the letter you
wrote to the district attorney

1076
00:45:17,002 --> 00:45:19,337
when you threatened
to expose me.

1077
00:45:19,422 --> 00:45:21,423
Expose you?
For what?

1078
00:45:21,474 --> 00:45:22,754
I never wrote
a letter like that.

1079
00:45:22,791 --> 00:45:25,226
I'm not recording you.

1080
00:45:25,294 --> 00:45:26,678
I don't need
to record you.

1081
00:45:26,762 --> 00:45:29,431
This letter was printed
from your hard drive,

1082
00:45:29,482 --> 00:45:32,300
which has your computer's
digital signature.

1083
00:45:35,688 --> 00:45:37,772
What do you want?

1084
00:45:37,823 --> 00:45:39,274
I wanna know,
if you had the chance,

1085
00:45:39,325 --> 00:45:40,641
would you have traded
that car

1086
00:45:40,693 --> 00:45:42,110
to get your parents
back together?

1087
00:45:43,312 --> 00:45:44,746
That's a stupid
goddamn question,

1088
00:45:44,813 --> 00:45:46,030
and you know it.

1089
00:45:46,115 --> 00:45:48,583
I never had that chance,
so what does it matter?

1090
00:45:48,650 --> 00:45:51,002
Because I do.

1091
00:45:51,087 --> 00:45:54,622
What do I want?

1092
00:45:54,673 --> 00:45:56,875
I wanna give
this office back.

1093
00:45:56,959 --> 00:45:59,461
I didn't earn it,
I don't want it,

1094
00:45:59,512 --> 00:46:01,592
and if there's a chance
it'll help Harvey forgive me,

1095
00:46:01,630 --> 00:46:03,598
I'm gonna take it.

1096
00:46:07,103 --> 00:46:09,554
Oh, and, uh,

1097
00:46:09,638 --> 00:46:12,774
if you ever do
send that letter,

1098
00:46:12,841 --> 00:46:15,777
you're in the same boat
as me.

1099
00:46:28,357 --> 00:46:30,191
Harvey,
you're looking determined.

1100
00:46:30,242 --> 00:46:32,827
- I am.
- What can I do for you?

1101
00:46:32,878 --> 00:46:35,880
Look, I know
we had an arrangement,

1102
00:46:35,965 --> 00:46:37,215
but I came here
to change it.

1103
00:46:37,299 --> 00:46:38,216
Change it?

1104
00:46:38,300 --> 00:46:39,968
But you might not even win.

1105
00:46:40,035 --> 00:46:42,637
I've just heard about
this new special prosecutor.

1106
00:46:42,704 --> 00:46:44,839
Relax, the case
was always gonna be hard.

1107
00:46:44,890 --> 00:46:46,141
It just got
a little harder.

1108
00:46:46,208 --> 00:46:47,475
Because you made it
that way.

1109
00:46:47,543 --> 00:46:48,810
That's my problem.

1110
00:46:48,877 --> 00:46:51,012
And now you're using
that increased difficulty

1111
00:46:51,063 --> 00:46:52,713
to renegotiate our deal.

1112
00:46:52,765 --> 00:46:56,651
That's your problem.

1113
00:46:56,718 --> 00:46:59,988
We both know
how important Ava is to you.

1114
00:47:01,740 --> 00:47:02,774
What do you want?

1115
00:47:02,858 --> 00:47:04,692
I don't wanna run
from a fight.

1116
00:47:04,743 --> 00:47:06,327
Meaning?

1117
00:47:06,395 --> 00:47:07,328
I win,

1118
00:47:07,396 --> 00:47:09,864
you don't fire me,

1119
00:47:09,915 --> 00:47:13,401
you back me
for managing partner.

1120
00:47:13,452 --> 00:47:16,904
You want
to take down Jessica.

1121
00:47:16,956 --> 00:47:18,696
Yes, I do.

